<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SHAW HAPPY TO BE STAYING
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE _ If Brian Shaw was at all unclear of his status with
the Los Angeles Lakers, he got all the reassurance he needed
Saturday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
   ``I came in today and I still had a number and a jersey in the
locker room, so I guess that means I'm here to stay,'' Shaw said
with a laugh.
</P>
<P>
   A few months ago, Shaw was just a short-term fill-in for an
injured Kobe Bryant. But when 3 p.m. passed Saturday, his contract
with the Lakers became guaranteed for the rest of the season,
effectively assuring he's here to stay.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was confident in my ability, if I had an opportunity to go
out and play, that I might be able to show at some point during the
season that I may be useful,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   More than useful, Shaw was the first guard off the bench for the
first month of the season and has since provided occasional scoring
bursts as the Lakers' fourth guard, behind Bryant, Ron Harper and
Derek Fisher.
</P>
<P>
   He's averaging 4 points, 2.6 rebounds and 2.1 assists in 15
minutes per game.
</P>
<P>
   Shaw nearly started the season unemployed after being traded
from Portland to the Houston Rockets, who waived him. Then the
Seattle Sonics brass took a pass on him.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was just joking with a couple guys on the Seattle team,
because the week before I worked out for the Lakers, I worked out
for Seattle. So some of the guys were saying, `Now you can laugh
and rub it in their faces, because you came and worked out for
them, and they didn't sign you. Now you signed with the Lakers, and
you guys are rolling and have the best record in the league.'
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm just happy to be in this situation and ready to contribute
whenever I'm called on.''
</P>
<P>
   Breaking out: Derek Fisher appeared to put a 2-for-30 slump
behind him Friday when he hit 4 of 10 shots for 13 points in the
Lakers' victory over the Charlotte Hornets. But he was cautious
about drawing any conclusions.
</P>
<P>
   ``I made a couple shots that I hadn't been making,'' he said,
``but that doesn't guarantee anything for (Saturday night) or
Monday. So I just have to take it one game at a time.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-09-00 0205EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
