   SPENDING-CUTS (Washington) _ The administration outlines where
it will make the modest spending cuts agreed to with Congress; it
concentrates on pork-barrel and earmarked projects favored by
lawmakers. By Robert Pear. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   ARMEDFORCES-STUDY (Washington) _ A two-year study of American
military culture by the Center for Strategic and International
Studies has found that the military has retained its `moral anchor'
but the people are under unacceptable strain from over-deployment,
and a lack of money, people, and resources at a time when the the
country has relied on the military as never before. By Elizabeth
Becker. 700 words.
