<HEADLINE>
BASEBALL'S IDIOTS GUIDE TO P.R.
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By STEVE DILBECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Major League Baseball looks like it's busy playing
the public relations game with its John Rocker mess.
</P>
<P>
   Since when does baseball reveal that it's ordered a player to
undergo psychological testing? For what, being an idiot?
</P>
<P>
   And if psychologists could rid the world of bigotry, what the
world needs is a hell of a lot more psychologists.
</P>
<P>
   __That said, what is up with Jesse Jackson? Ray Rhodes is fired
after an 8-8 season because he's African-American?
</P>
<P>
   How about because _ as they discovered when fired by the Eagles
last year _ he's not a very good coach?
</P>
<P>
   The Packers missed the playoffs for the first time in seven
years. And if it's racial, remember these are the same people who
hired him.
</P>
<P>
   __Maybe if we see that replay of the surreal Titans-Bills final
play another 10 times, it finally won't look like a forward pass.
</P>
<P>
   Either way, it doesn't bode well down the playoff road for
Taft's Jeff Fisherthat his Titans had to squeak out a victory at
home on a miracle finish.
</P>
<P>
   __Tonya Harding and ice: The world really doesn't need further
evidence of a wrong match.
</P>
<P>
   __Is Billy Knight with UCLA today?
</P>
<P>
   __What's more fashionable these days, Hollywood blondes turning
Hollywood brunettes or the Mighty Ducks blowing another power play?
</P>
<P>
   __Given their success, it's hard to argue Scotty Pippen hasn't
been a strong addition to the Blazers, but his numbers aren't
making for a convincing story. Although he leads Portland in
assists at 5.3 per game, he is only third in scoring (12.9), third
in rebounding (6.8) and tops in turnovers (2.7).
</P>
<P>
   __Seen sitting courtside about 25 seats away from each other at
last week's second Lakers-Clippers games at the Staples Center were
your former rival NFL L.A. owners in waiting, Ed Roski Jr. and
Michael Ovitz. Just like old times, only without blueprints and
spin.
</P>
<P>
   __One of the things we like best about Phil Jackson as Lakers
coach is the way he's not afraid to criticize his players, even
glamour boys like Kobe Bryant.
</P>
<P>
   And anyone who thinks their current 14-game winning streak means
there's no way the Lakers would now trade free-agent-to-be Glen
Rice need only harken back to last year.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers were riding a 10-game streak when Jerry West traded
Eddie Jones and Elden Campbell to Charlotte last year for Rice and
J.R. Reid.
</P>
<P>
   __Let's see, Al Davis wants $800 million from Oakland/Alameda
County for broken promises and $700 million from the NFL for giving
up his supposed rights to the L.A. market.
</P>
<P>
   Maybe Irwindale escaped cheap.
</P>
<P>
   __How could the Dodgers' Single-A team in San Bernardino hire
Jack Clark as their hitting coach without naming Tom Niedenfuer
pitching coach?
</P>
<P>
   __Is it just us, or does every time TV uses a camera from behind
to view a punt, it looks like the punter shanks it?
</P>
<P>
   __So much for parity. Those blowouts of the 8-8 Lions and
Cowboys in the first round of the playoffs didn't exactly enhance
the NFL's postseason.
</P>
<P>
   Memo to Barry Sanders: You were right after all.
</P>
<P>
   __Wonder if Marge Schott has ever met Rocker.
</P>
<P>
   __The Rams might have gone 1-2 against teams with winning
records this year, but they were 8-0 at home and won by an average
margin of 25 points. And they have the homefield advantage
throughout.
</P>
<P>
   __Ah, winter is in the air. The Dodgers open their annual winter
workouts this morning. With renovations going on at Dodger Stadium,
this year the volunteer workouts will be held at USC.
</P>
<P>
   The old pasty guy will be Orel Hershiser.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers sure have worked hard to fill that right-handed
middle-relief need this offseason. Now if only they could do
something about that problem at second base, center, catcher and
the rotation.
</P>
<P>
   __If Steve Lavin thinks he's been under heat now, he'll think
he's fallen into Death Valley on an August afternoon if UCLA
stumbles at the Sports Arena against USC on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Maybe he can get Erica Gomez to talk to the boys.
</P>
<P>
   __Now we understand. GM Bill Stoneman is just confused. He
thinks he was hired as the Angels' farm director.
</P>
</TEXT>
